The article starts strong and then torpedoes itself with the collapsible. It should be about the life and times of an immortal who has to piece together his own history. Instead, you awkwardly pivot to the horrors of genocide, barely expand upon what was already said in 1000, and give little or no thought to 5888's role in that event or how it defined him. SCP-4000 explore the horror and impact genocide in a much more dynamic and meaningful way. If you want to explore genocide, do that in a different article. Don't shackle this one to your clumsy attempt.





